@*
PSEUDOCODE / PLAN (detailed):
1. This partial will expose a small snippet to render the existing SVG at:
   - wwwroot/images/Rectangle-left.svg
2. Provide two safe, accessible rendering options:
   - <img> element referencing the static file (recommended for simple use).
   - <object> element for fallback/interactive needs (keeps it external).
3. Ensure sizing is responsive and constrained to the SVG's height (205px).
4. Provide minimal CSS scoped to the snippet to avoid global side effects.
5. Document expected usage in a short Razor comment so callers know how to include it.
*@

@* Usage:
   In a Razor Page or View:
     <partial name="~/Pages/Shared/_RectangleLeftImage.cshtml" />
   or
     @await Html.PartialAsync("_RectangleLeftImage")
*@

@* MARKUP: simple <img> (preferred) with optional <object> alternative *@
<div class="rectangle-left-component">
    <!-- Simple img reference to the file in wwwroot/images -->
    <img src="~/images/Rectangle-left.svg"
         alt="Decorative rectangle"
         class="rectangle-left-img" />

    <!-- Alternative: object tag if you need to target inner SVG or allow clicking into SVG document.
         Uncomment if you need scriptable/interactive SVG access.
    <object data="~/images/Rectangle-left.svg" type="image/svg+xml" class="rectangle-left-object" aria-label="Decorative rectangle"></object>
    -->
</div>

<style>
    /* Scoped styles for this partial */
    .rectangle-left-component {
        display: inline-block;
        line-height: 0; /* prevent descender gaps under inline images */
    }

    /* Constrain to original height and scale width proportionally.
       Adjust height as needed; using max-height keeps it responsive. */
    .rectangle-left-img,
    .rectangle-left-object {
        height: 205px;          /* match SVG's exported height */
        max-width: 100%;        /* avoid overflow on small viewports */
        width: auto;
        display: block;
    }

    /* Optional: make the image decorative for screen readers if purely visual:
       - Remove alt text and add aria-hidden="true" where appropriate.
       Keep meaningful alt text if it carries information.
    */
</style>